parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Door Malfunction - Unlatched Door While Driving
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The door opening while driving can cause a loss of control, accidents, or injuries to occupants, as well as damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The front passenger-side door opens unexpectedly while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield seal can cause water to leak into the vehicle, leading to electrical issues, mold growth, and damage to interior components.
symptoms: Water leaks into the vehicle through the windshield
often during rain or car washes
causing water to accumulate on the dashboard

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield seal can cause water to enter the vehicle, impairing vision and creating a safety concern while driving in rain or snow. Additionally, water dripping on the controls can be a distraction and further compromise safety.
symptoms: Water enters the vehicle through the windshield
water drips down on the controls
water comes in from openings along the roof.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A leaking windshield can cause water to enter the vehicle, potentially damaging electrical components, carpets, and upholstery. A loose windshield can also compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to safety concerns in the event of an accident.

Unintended acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially if the vehicle surges forward unexpectedly. This can lead to loss of control, collisions, and damage to the vehicle and surrounding property.
The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to use, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: the seat belt cannot be extended
the seat belt retractor fails to release properly
the seat belt is too short to use.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Control Module (TCM) Error Code P074468
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The error code P074468 can cause the transmission to shift jerkily, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: transmission may need to be reset.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The random downshifting of the transmission while braking can cause the vehicle to lose control, especially on slippery roads, leading to accidents.
symptoms: vehicle loses control when slowing down at 10-15 mph.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unidentified transmission issue can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, especially on slippery roads.
symptoms: vehicle loses control when slowing down at 10-15 mph.
